          <h2>Rules & Regulations</h2>
    
          <!-- Club Mania (1st Semester) -->
          <div class="event">
              <h3>General Rules :-</h3>
              <p>
                 Eligibility: The event is open to all registered college students.<br>
                 Registration: Participants must register before the event date. No on-the-spot registrations will be allowed.<BR>
                 Entry Fee: ₹30 per participant.<BR>
                 Timing: Participants must be present at the venue 10 minutes before their scheduled time.<br>
                 No External Aids: The use of phones, notes, or any other reference materials is strictly prohibited during preparation and delivery.<BR>
                 Fair Play: Participants must not disturb others during their preparation or speech delivery.<br>
                 Compliance: It is mandatory for every participant to read all the guidelines and follow the rules and regulations accordingly.
              </p>
              <h3>Specific Guidelines :-</h3>
              <p>
                 Round 1 - Qualifiers:<br>
                   o Participants are shown a general topic on the screen.<br>
                   o Preparation Time: 3 minutes.<br>
                   o Speech Time: 2 minutes.<br>
                   o Judges will evaluate based on content relevance, fluency, confidence, and engagement.<br>
                 Round 2 - Finals:<br>
                   o The top participants from Round 1 advance to the finals.<br>
                   o Topics in this round will be more challenging.<br>
                   o Preparation Time: 2 minutes.<br>
                   o Speech Time: 3-4 minutes.<br>
                   o Additional judging criteria include originality of thought and persuasiveness.
              </p>
              <h3>Judging Criteria :-</h3>
              <p>
                 Content Relevance: How well the speech aligns with the given topic.<br>
                 Fluency: Smoothness of speech without unnecessary pauses or fillers.<br>
                 Confidence: Clarity, volume, and assurance in delivery.<br>
                 Engagement: Ability to capture and maintain the audience’s attention.<br>
                 Originality of Thought (Final Round): Creativity in the approach to the topic.<br>
                 Persuasiveness (Final Round): The effectiveness in conveying ideas convincingly.<br>
                Scoring System:<br>
                 o Content Relevance: 20 points<br>
                 o Fluency: 20 points<br>
                 o Confidence: 20 points<br>
                 o Engagement: 20 points<br>
                 o Originality of Thought (Finals Only): 10 points<br>
                 o Persuasiveness (Finals Only): 10 points
              </p>
              <h3>Code of Conduct :-</h3>
              <p>
                 Respect: All participants and attendees must maintain respect toward others.<br>
                 Professionalism: Participants must refrain from using offensive language or making inappropriate remarks.<br>
                 Time Limits: Exceeding the allotted preparation or speech time may result in point deductions.<br>
                 Sportsmanship: Participants are expected to applaud others' performances and show appreciation
              </p>
              <h3>Disqualification Condition :-</h3>
              <p>
                 Plagiarism: Copying content from external sources will result in immediate disqualification.<br>
                 Offensive Content: Any speech containing offensive language, hate speech, or derogatory remarks will lead to disqualification.<br>
                 Non-compliance: Failure to adhere to the rules, including using prohibited materials or exceeding time limits excessively.<br>
                 Unprofessional Behaviour: Disrupting other participants or judges during the event
              </p>
              <h3>Safety Measures :-</h3>
